Package at.fhhagenberg.sqe.elevator.wrappers

Interface IElevatorWrapper

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Remote
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ElevatorWrapperImpl
    public interface IElevatorWrapper
extends Remote
    Wrapper around IElevator Object, which can be adjusted when the IElevator API changes.

      • getCommittedDirection

        int getCommittedDirection​(int elevatorNumber)
                   throws RemoteException
        Retrieves the committed direction of the specified elevator (up / down / uncommitted).
        Parameters:
        elevatorNumber - - elevator number whose committed direction is being retrieved
        Returns:
        the current direction of the specified elevator where up=0, down=1 and uncommitted=2
        Throws:
        RemoteException

      • getElevatorAccel

        int getElevatorAccel​(int elevatorNumber)
              throws RemoteException
        Provides the current acceleration of the specified elevator in feet per sec^2.
        Parameters:
        elevatorNumber - - elevator number whose acceleration is being retrieved
        Returns:
        returns the acceleration of the indicated elevator where positive speed is acceleration and negative is deceleration
        Throws:
        RemoteException

      • getElevatorButton

        boolean getElevatorButton​(int elevatorNumber,
                          int floor)
                   throws RemoteException
        Provides the status of a floor request button on a specified elevator (on/off).
        Parameters:
        elevatorNumber - - elevator number whose button status is being retrieved
        floor - - floor number button being checked on the selected elevator
        Returns:
        returns boolean to indicate if floor button on the elevator is active (true) or not (false)
        Throws:
        RemoteException

      • setCustomSocketTimeout

        void setCustomSocketTimeout​(int timeout)
                     throws IOException
        Needed to avoid blocking of GUI due to way to long polling timeout on the RMI socket. Especially needed for windows (default timeout 15 seconds).
        Parameters:
        timeout - Maximum timeout in ms.
        Throws:
        IOException
